transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hey, thanks for calling Viagra. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yeah, I just needed to refill my prescription.

Speaker 1: Okay, yeah, I can help you out. What was your first name, last name, date of birth, please?

Speaker 2: David Bennett. B. E. N. N. E. T. T.

Speaker 1: 05 15 1959?

Speaker 2: Perfect, perfect. Then did you want to do that?

Speaker 1: You look like you got 50 pills for the first time with an upgrade, so we don't do 50 pills at a time.

Speaker 2: But if you wanted to do the original 25?

Speaker 1: Definitely can't do that for you again, or if you wanted to go up to do 40 pills, can also do that, okay?

Speaker 2: So just depends how many you want to get.

Speaker 1: I'm sorry, so did you want to do 40 pills or 25?

Speaker 2: Yeah, 25 is fine, perfect, perfect. All righty, and then are you still there at 216 Mira Loma Drive, Oroville?

Speaker 1: Nine five nine six five.

Speaker 2: Yes, but—

Speaker 1: Could you give me the last four of the credit card you have on file?

Speaker 2: 9696. It's a Visa. Yeah, I've got a different one though.

Speaker 1: Okay, I can take that new card number whenever you're ready.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: How much is it going to be?

Speaker 2: For 25, 113.95.

Speaker 1: You—

Speaker 2: Okay, it's 4 1 4 7.

Speaker 1: 3 4 2 0 8.

Speaker 2: 9 9 9.

Speaker 1: 1 3 8 6.

Speaker 2: Expiration?

Speaker 1: It's 6 30 and the CVV code 7 4 7.

Speaker 2: All righty, give me just a second.

Speaker 1: I'll place this order for you now.

Speaker 2: And you are all set there, Mr. Benny. Order has been placed. You see that process, you can arrive in the next few business days.

Speaker 1: Great, appreciate it. Thank you. Bye.

Speaker 2: Bye now. Thank you.
